          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName>
                                        <date>March 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5613/1853</date>.</p>
                              <p>Dear sir and friend!</p>
                              <p>I transmit you herewith an advertisement which you<lb/> will please
                                        to insert in your Occident for <date><hi rend="underline"
                                                  >April</hi></date> if it<lb/> arrives in time. I
                                        will <add>Hebrew</add> come myself to <placeName>New
                                                  York</placeName><lb/> and would be very glad to
                                        find you there. My Dear father who<lb/> will arrive there—I
                                        hope—about the <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of
                                                  April</date> would also<lb/> be very happy to make
                                        your acquaintance and if you agree<lb/> to take part of his
                                        stock of hebrew books in commisison<lb/> he would probably
                                        give you all inducement&amp; facilities possible.<lb/> A
                                        notice, about as follows would perhaps be proper in your
                                        Occident<lb/> “Large arrived of hebrew Books.</p>
                              <p><persName>Mr. I. I. Bush</persName> the father of <persName
                                                  role="author">Mr Isidor Bush</persName> now in
                                                  <placeName>St Louis</placeName><lb/> who has been
                                        for many years the proprietor of the largest Hebrew<lb/>
                                        Printing Establishment (v. Schmidt in
                                                  <placeName>Vienna</placeName>) and has edited a
                                        great<lb/> number of valuable hebrew works is expected to
                                        arrive this month from <placeName>Vienna</placeName>.<lb/>
                                        The old gentleman wishes to pass the evening of his life
                                        with<lb/> his only son in this home of the free; and we bid
                                        him welcome.<lb/> He brings with him a large assortment of
                                        hebrew Books,<lb/> mostly Bibles and Prayerbooks for the
                                        german and polish minhag<lb/>
                                        <sic>ellegantly</sic> bound. As <persName>Mr Bush</persName>
                                        intends to go west and to<lb/> stay a few days only at
                                                  <placeName>New York</placeName>, we call the
                                        attention of<lb/> those who deal in Sphorim, and others who
                                        want to purchase<lb/> to his advertisement.</p>
                              <p>In regard to congregational affairs I request you to insert<lb/>
                                        the following communications filling the blank
                                        according<lb/> to your <sic>judgement</sic>, as you have
                                        certainly received the printed<lb/> copy of the
                                        constitution, which I have sent you.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>A good Translation of the Introduction or Preamble on Ist
                                        Article<lb/> would perhaps be of some interest to the public
                                        at large<lb/> and your readers in particular and would at
                                        the same time be<lb/> very <sic>wellcome</sic> to us here,
                                        as we intend to print our constitution<lb/> in English also
                                        and a correct translation—in spirit more than word—<lb/>
                                        would be a task which I could not undertake to solve.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName>—The Bnai-El
                                        congregation, lately formed by a union<lb/> of two former
                                        congregations here, have adopted a
                                        constitution...<lb/>............<lb/>..........<lb/> and
                                        duly elected there after the following gentlemen as Trustees<lb/>
                                        <persName role="author">Mr. I. Bush</persName>, <persName>D
                                                  Block</persName>, <persName>Is. Lowman</persName>,
                                                  <persName>A Suss</persName>, <persName>L
                                                  Schwarzkopf</persName>, <persName>B
                                                  Singer</persName><lb/> and <persName>W
                                                  Walter</persName>, from whom <persName>Mr
                                                  Walter</persName> has been appointed President<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr Suss</persName> Secretary <persName>Mr
                                                  Lowman</persName> Treasurer. There have been
                                        also<lb/> elected different committees: one for the erecting
                                        of a Syna<lb/>gogue and getting up a subscription to that
                                        effect, one for a better<lb/> organization of the Ritual,
                                        one committee for the burial of<lb/> the dead, and so on. It
                                        is to be hoped that the com<lb/>mittees and officers will
                                        perform their respective duties with<lb/> pious zeal and
                                        promote thereby the objects expressed by<lb/> their
                                        constitution. <persName>Mr L Schwarzkopf</persName> has been
                                        elected<lb/> Chasan of the congregation and the service is
                                        well attended<lb/> on every <date>sabbath</date> since.</p>
                              <p>Dear Sir—full liberty is given to you to speak more on these<lb/>
                                        subjects or to change the wording—according to your
                                        best<lb/> belief. For the ,,advertisements” I will pay you,
                                        of course</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">very respectfully your friend &amp; servant</p>
                              <p rend="indent(11)">
                                        <persName role="author">Isidore Bush</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">Advertisement:</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">The largest stock of</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <hi rend="underline">Hebrew Books</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">that was probably ever brought to this
                                        country</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">is to arrive during these days (about
                                                  <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of
                                        April</date>)</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">and will be sold, wholesale, <hi
                                                  rend="underline">at very low prices</hi></p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">It contains chumashin, Tenachs, Machsorin</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">Tefillas &amp;c, &amp;c. of the celebrated
                                                  <placeName>Vienna</placeName> Editor,</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">all bound in very elegant <sic>stile</sic></p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">Dealers in <add>?</add> will never find again
                                        such a favorable opor</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">tunity and will do well therefore to call
                                        personally or give</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">orders to their <placeName>New
                                                  York</placeName> friends, to purchase for
                                        them;</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">it being the intention of the Importer
                                                  <persName><hi rend="underline">Mr I. I.
                                                  Bush</hi></persName></p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">from <placeName>Vienna</placeName>, to dispose
                                        of them during <hi rend="underline">a few days</hi> for
                                        cash</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">on good, approved paper. The place of sale
                                        will</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">probably be at <persName>Mr
                                                  Petshaw's</persName> Bookstore, or if
                                        elsewhere</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">will be advertised in the daily Papers.</p>
